<div class="entry-title"><h1>Notes on Diegetic Game Rules</h1></div>
<div class="entry-meta"><p>Last updated on 2024-05-20</p></div>
<div class="entry-content"><h2 id="an-anti-canonical-ludological-atlas-of-our-sphere">An Anti-Canonical Ludological Atlas of <em>Our Sphere</em></h2>

<h3 id="playing-at-the-sphere">Playing at the Sphere</h3>

<p>Some Dawnlanders reportedly have developed a fine way of passing on the knowledge of their people: via their highly-developed ludological faculties, or, put plainly, through the playing of games.</p>

<p>These Dawnlanders gather statistical approximation devices of various sorts, although intricate polyhedronic assemblages &amp; finely-decorated cuttings of pressed &amp; dried pulp are most common.</p>

<p>There are several versions of this game played across the Dawnlands; here, I describe the one sometimes called <em>Mythic Bastionland</em>, so named for an old Magicotechnologigarchical term.</p>
</div>
